TSLA.title: Gamma Pivot at $450, Volatility Dampened
TSLA.body: TSLA is trading precisely at the $450 strike, which exhibits significant gamma interest on both call and put sides, acting as a pivotal point. Net GEX is positive, indicating dealers are long gamma, which should contribute to price stability and range-bound trading. The primary Put Wall is at $400, offering strong support, while the Call Wall at $500 acts as resistance. No significant change in Net GEX from yesterday, maintaining the current structure.

SPY.title: Short Gamma Amplifies Volatility; $680 Support Critical
SPY.body: SPY is characterized by a substantially negative Net GEX, indicating dealers are short gamma. This market regime is conducive to amplified price movements and increased volatility. Price is currently at $681.92, trading just above a massive Put GEX strike at $680, which functions as immediate support. A break below $680 could trigger an accelerated move lower. The next significant Call GEX is at $690, presenting overhead resistance. The broader Call Wall is at $700, with the Put Wall at $595. No significant change in Net GEX from yesterday, maintaining the current structure.
